    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-10-26T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-10-26T20:00:00-05:00" n="868"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d868">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.51/10–2645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shaw</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-10-26T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 26, 1945—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 26—4:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>766. For Export-Import Bank from Applegate. Due to delays and lack of interest in
                    certain government departments regarding plans for reorganization, approval of
                    reforms of statutes and payment to corporation of 5 percent commission, interest
                    and installment due on investment in Quevedo–Manta project, Mr. Shaw, Chargé
                    d’Affaires Embassy arranged appointment for me with Minister Trujillo<note
                        n="38" xml:id="d868fn38">José Vicente Trujillo, Minister of Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> with whom I discussed the whole situation and he informed
                    the President<note n="39" xml:id="d868fn39">José Maria Velasco Ibarra.</note> of
                    the situation with the result of immediate action by <pb facs="1071" n="1057"
                        xml:id="pg_1057"/> Minister of Economy. In session yesterday afternoon and
                    this morning with Minister Economy [and] representative of Foreign Office
                    reforms of statutes were approved and tentative plans for reorganization made by
                    which Govt agreed to reimburse corporation for assets to be transferred, also to
                    study means to furnish funds for Quevedo-Manta continued construction. …
                    [Applegate.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shaw</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
